quran[27]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,127,"But they denied him [Iliyâs (Elias)], so they will certainly be brought forth (to the punishment),",""
  37,128,"Except the chosen slaves of Allâh.",""
  37,129,"And We left for him (a goodly remembrance) among the later generations.",""
  37,130,"""Salâm (peace) be upon Ilyâsîn (Elias)!""",""
  37,131,"Verily, thus do We reward the Muhsinûn (good-doers, who perform good deeds totally for Allâh’s sake only - See V.2:112).",""
  37,132,"Verily, he was one of Our believing slaves.",""
  37,133,"And verily, Lût (Lot) was one of the Messengers.",""
  37,134,"When We saved him and his family, all,",""
  37,135,"Except an old woman (his wife) who was among those who remained behind.",""
  37,136,"Then We destroyed the rest (the town of Sodom at the place of the Dead Sea now in Palestine).",""
  37,137,"Verily, you pass by them in the morning",""
  37,138,"And at night; will you not then reflect?",""
  37,139,"And, verily, Yûnus (Jonah) was one of the Messengers.",""
  37,140,"When he ran to the laden ship:",""
  37,141,"Then he (agreed to) cast lots, and he was among the losers.",""
  37,142,"Then a (big) fish swallowed him as he had done an act worthy of blame.",""
  37,143,"Had he not been of them who glorify Allâh,",""
  37,144,"He would have indeed remained inside its belly (the fish) till the Day of Resurrection.",""
  37,145,"But We cast him forth on the naked shore while he was sick,",""
  37,146,"And We caused a plant of gourd to grow over him.",""
  37,147,"And We sent him to a hundred thousand (people) or even more.",""
  37,148,"And they believed; so We gave them enjoyment for a while.",""
  37,149,"Now ask them (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): ""Are there (only) daughters for your Lord and sons for them?""",""
  37,150,"Or did We create the angels female while they were witnesses?",""
  37,151,"Verily, it is of their falsehood that they (Quraish pagans) say:",""
  37,152,"""Allâh has begotten [offspring - the angels being the daughters of Allâh)?"" And, verily, they are liars!",""
  37,153,"Has He (then) chosen daughters rather than sons?",""
